main event: A civilian reported seeing one or possibly two unidentified objects in the sky over Pleasant Hill, Missouri on August 12, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were observed for 25 minutes and exhibited changing colors of red, green, and white, The objects appeared stationary before later drifting southwest and then disappearing to the west, The report mentions that the object size was similar to that of a star, There was a possible second object observed close to the first, The visibility conditions were clear with a distant altitude estimated between 4,000 to 5,000 feet.
sighted object: one or possibly two unidentified flying objects
witness description: civilian observer in Pleasant Hill, Missouri
